{"id":1073916266,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"8Â months","timestamp":1697162719,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1073916266/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"43.5 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        int len = s.length();\n        int[] arr = new int[len];\n\n        int res = 0;\n\n        for(int i=0; i<len; i++){\n\n            char ch = s.charAt(i);\n\n            if(ch=='I') arr[i]=1;\n            else if(ch=='V') arr[i] = 5;\n            else if(ch=='X') arr[i] = 10;\n            else if(ch=='L') arr[i] = 50;\n            else if(ch=='C') arr[i] = 100;\n            else if(ch=='D') arr[i] = 500;\n            else if(ch=='M') arr[i] = 1000;\n        }\n\n        for(int i=0; i<len-1; i++){\n\n            if(arr[i]<arr[i+1])\n                res-=arr[i];\n            else \n                res+=arr[i];\n        }\n\n        return res+arr[len-1];\n\n\n\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
